      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RITZA OLD MATE (1) resumed in a Grade 4/5 at Geelong and ran into the frame when second over 400m (22.53). Goes very well at the trip finding the frame in each of four starts. Recorded one of the quickest times on the card last start despite being beaten. Capable of going well again. GOBLIN (4) is a well performed sprinter ideally suited at the shorter trips. Was a bit beyond her last time when fifth (30.41) over 515m at Sandown in a Grade 5 but is better suited here over less ground. Has a strong record at this distance including six wins. Leading chance. ASTON CLEESE (2) boasts a strong record this journey here with five wins and two minors from 13 tries. Recorded a half a length win (22.23) in a Grade 5 last time at this track. Looks suited here and can measure up. PAW DANGER (5) is likely to have admirers.",
